      },
      {
        "id": "b",
        "content": "False"
      }
    ],
    "correctAnswerId": "b",
    "explanation": "In the Nominal Group Technique, members present ideas orally, write them on a board for all to see, and discuss them simultaneously, which requires meeting face to face. It is the Delphi Technique that gathers ideas from members who are geographically separated and do not meet face to face.",
    "reference": "Textbook Page 195: \"In contrast to the nominal group technique or brainstorming, the Delphi technique does not have group members meet face to face.\"",
